1. e4 c5 2. c3 d5 3. exd5 Qxd5 4. d4 e6 5. Nf3 Nf6 6. Na3 Nc6
{ One of the significant alternatives in this position.   Black keeps the queen on d5 unless White forces him to go back with Nb5. He holds the bishop on f8 to avoid a loss of tempo after Nb5-Qd8/Qd7-dxc5. }
7. Be3
{ We stay noncommittal with Nb5/Bc4/Nc4 plans and give the threat to take on c5 instead and force Black to decide on the center. }
7... cxd4
{ The main idea of Black. He now wants to eliminate the knight on a3. } 8. Nb5
{ The point of White's setup. The knight leaves an exposed position on a3, gaining time in the process. The threat of Nc7 forces Black to move his queen, losing precious time. }
8... Qd8 { The more natural retreat for the queen. } 9. Nbxd4
{ The first position to give Black an illusion of choice. There are lots of lines, but some of them are plain bad. White's lead in development forces Black to be very precise.  For instance,  9...Bd7  looks pretty tempting and solid, not damaging our pawn structure, but after  10.Nxc6  Bxc6  11.Qxd8  Black cannot recapture with rook as the pawn on a7 falls, and recapturing with the king exposes the king after White castles long and plays Ne5.   9...Be7  10.Nxc6  breaks Black's pawn structure, and after the queen trade, White puts immediate pressure on the pawn with moves like Ne5 and enjoys a pleasant position. }
9... Nxd4 10. Bxd4
{ White's bishop gets an excellent spot where it cannot be moved away quickly. }
10... Be7
{ Wanting to castle seems like the logical way.   10...Qc7  11.Be5  doesn't give peace to the queen. }
11. Bd3
{ Anticipating Black's castle on the kingside, White's bishops have taken their ideal places. }
11... O-O 12. Qe2
{ We would like to castle on the other side and start attacking the kingside. }
12... Qa5 { Black finds a way to stop us from going to the queenside. } 13. Ne5
{ We adapt to the new situation and change our plans. Now we will castle short and claim the queen on a5 is misplaced.   White's pieces are harmoniously placed and have more space. Thus White's advantage is indisputable. }
