[Black "2...Nc6 3.d4 e6"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. c3 Nc6
{ This move intends to play d5 next but doesn't stop White from playing d4, which is the main idea of Alapin.   So there are no marks for guessing our next move 😊. }
3. d4
{ White continues with the most obvious plan of taking control of the center. }
3... e6
{ A bit too naive, and it is one of the rare occurrences when after normal looking first three moves, engines are screaming with +1.30 for White 😊.   The reasoning is straightforward, as White now gets d5 with a tempo. }
4. d5 { Gaining more space with a tempo. } 4... exd5 5. exd5 Ne5
{ Black hopes to get some activity due to his knight on e5, but that is his only active piece in the position. }
6. Nf3
{ Exchanging Black's only active piece seems like a simple solution to get an almost winning position. }
6... Nxf3+ 7. Qxf3
{ With Bd3 and O-O coming next, Black gets into huge trouble now. } 7... d6 8.
Bd3
{ Black has nothing to show for White's huge space advantage. Engines call this winning for White, but let's be modest and say that White is clearly better. }
*

