3... cxd4
{ 3...d5  4.exd5  Qxd5  is coveredhere in the Alapin 2... d5 section. } 4. cxd4
d6
{ Does absolutely nothing to stop White in the center of the board.   4...g6  would be even worse because after  5.d5  Black can neither play  5...Ne5  6.f4  which traps the knight nor @@StartFEN@@r1bqkbnr/pp1ppp1p/2n3p1/3P4/4P3/8/PP3PPP/RNBQKBNR b KQkq - 0 5@@EndFEN@@  5...Nb8  6.Qd4  which helps us to develop our pieces in a natural way. }
5. d5
{ Engine's +2 might seem exaggerating, but hard to come up with an argument for Black's passive position. }
5... Ne5 6. f4 { The worst Alekhine Defense we have ever seen.😉 } 6... Nd7 7.
Nf3
{ It is surprising to see that 15 games have reached this position! What was Black thinking? }
7... Ngf6 8. Nc3
{ White will quickly finish his development and start a decisive attack.  White is clearly winning and purely for fun let's underline that engines think the best move for Black here is to play  8...g5  and give an evaluation of +4.56 😊. }
