3... Nc6 { Otherwise White gets d4 easily. } 4. Bc4
{ A nice developing move, targeting both weaknesses in Black's position, the d5-square and the f7-pawn. }
4... Nf6
{ By far the sharpest response and Black's only hope for equality. Other moves accept being worse. }
5. Ng5 { The most direct approach to hit on f7. } 5... d5
{ Otherwise, Black can as well resign. } 6. exd5 Nxd5 7. Qh5
{ White is forcing Black to walk a very narrow path.  The tempting  7.Nxf7  Kxf7  8.Qf3  Ke6  leads to unnecessary complications where Black has his resources. }
