11. Qe3
{ White is not interested in the queen trade when Black is hugely behind in development. }
11... Be6 { Offering further piece trade. } 12. Bf3
{ White keeps more pieces on the board since Black's king remains in the center. }
12... Nc6 13. d3 Rd8
{ A very natural plan to put pressure on d3, but Black still ends with huge problems }
14. Be4
{ White wants to take on c6 eventually to break Black's pawn structure, but this intermediate move forces Black's queen to go to a worse square. }
14... Qh5 15. Bxc6+
{ Creating very serious pawn weaknesses in the opponent's structure } 15...
bxc6 16. Nd2
{ With Ne4 coming next and having such a vulnerable pawn structure, Black will sustain some damage here. }
