[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. c3 a6
{ This move is better than it looks but fails, perhaps not surprisingly, to equalize. Black stays noncommittal for now and waits for White to charge in the center first. }
3. d4 { Not a surprise when we play Alapin 😊. } 3... d5
{ This is plain bad as White now takes on c5. } 4. dxc5 dxe4 5. Qxd8+
{ Better than taking the pawn with Qa4-Qxe4 which gives only slight edge 😊. }
5... Kxd8 6. Nd2 { Developing with a tempo aiming for e4 and c4-b6. } 6... Nf6
7. Nc4 { Heading for the b6-square. } 7... Nbd7 8. b4
{ As frequently seen in the Alapin, the pawn on c5 turns out to be an asset. Black's position remains cramped, with the king in the center. White is close to winning here. }
