{ 4...Qxd5  will transpose to the Alapin 2... d5 segment, which we will examinehere.  The position after  4...exd5  is essential for us to understand. In most cases, White will take on c5, resulting in a position with an isolated pawn on d5. Our task is to exchange some pieces, block the pawn firmly with a knight on  d4  , and win the endgame.  In most Alapin lines, White plays with the isolated pawn, not against it. The great variety of possible structures arising from the Alapin will improve your feel for many different positions and make you a better player, at least, that's the general idea 😊.  An important trick to know is after  4...cxd4  5.Bb5  Bd7  White has the cute  6.dxe6  Bxb5  7.exf7  Kxf7  8.Qb3  and the b5-bishop falls when White retains a material advantage. }
5. Bb5+
{ Simple chess. White goes for the fastest development, with Nf3 and O-O to follow in short succession.   And as for having maybe to exchange that bishop - we don't really mind some exchanges, as they bring us closer to the d5-pawn. }
5... Bd7
{ Somewhat less popular, but a possible move. Exchanging this bishop makes d5 potentially more vulnerable, but White still has to work plenty to prove it. Players who get isolated pawns would like to avoid piece exchanges in general. }
6. Bxd7+ { Otherwise, we lose time to defend that bishop on b5. } 6... Nxd7 7.
Nf3 Ngf6
{ Black tries to finish development and castle. He didn't have time to play  7...c4  as after  8.O-O  Ngf6  9.Re1  Be7  10.Qe2  his king will be stuck in the center for a while. }
8. O-O Be7 9. Nh4
{ Not at all strictly necessary, but still a very nice new idea! We like discovering new paths in chess whenever possible. White gets to play Nf5, which opens many new possibilities.  It was perfectly fine to play  9.dxc5  Nxc5  10.Be3  , which also promises White a better position due to Black's pawn structure. }
9... c4
{ An interesting way to avoid an isolated pawn, but can be quite risky too. }
10. Nf5 O-O 11. Bf4 { The bishop is well-placed here. } 11... Re8 12. Nd2
{ And White has a lot of interesting ways to proceed here with threats like g4 and Qf3. Black won't find navigating these waters easy, given that it's a new line. }
