{ After  15...Rxb2  16.Bc3  Rb6  White wins an exchange with  17.Qb8  Qd8  18.Qxd8  Kxd8  19.Ba5  . }
16. Qe3
{ The brilliant point of forcing the queen to c7 before playing Qe3 gets clear in the variation  16...Ne4  17.Nc3  when Black has no time to defend the d5-pawn and castle on time. }
