[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "6) 2...e6 3.d4 d5 Main Lines"]
[Black "7.dxc5 Bxc5 8.O-O Nf6 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. c3 e6 3. d4 d5 4. exd5 exd5 5. Bb5+ Nc6 6. Nf3 Bd6
{ All alternatives before this move are covered under the sidelines.   Black finishes his development and does not mind wasting a tempo with Bd6-Bxc5 in case White takes on c5. }
7. dxc5
{ Whenever Black moves the bishop from f8, it makes sense to take on c5 to force Black to waste a tempo. }
7... Bxc5 8. O-O Nf6
{ This line has become popular in recent times, the World Champion played it twice already in 2022.  The same position could also occur from a different move order with @@StartFEN@@r1bqkbnr/pp3ppp/2n5/1Bpp4/3P4/2P2N2/PP3PPP/RNBQK2R b KQkq - 3 6@@EndFEN@@  6...Nf6  7.O-O  Be7  8.dxc5  Bxc5  .  The knight is more active on f6, but Black also takes serious risks due to the upcoming pin with Bg5 and the open e-file. }
9. Bg5 { Pinning the knight, but also directly threatening the pawn on d5. }
9... O-O
{ This radical move was tried a few times, especially in online rapid and blitz. Magnus also tried it in the Chessable Masters Rapid 2022.   It is more of a rapid/blitz weapon with a lot of surprise value. In reality, Black just gets worse after some precise play by White. }
10. Bxf6 Qxf6
{ Black didn't castle to ruin the kingside structure with gxf6. The main idea is to sacrifice the pawn and play for activity. }
11. Qxd5 Bb6
{ Black's argument is that he will get some tempos against White's queen, and he has a pair of bishops. As we will see, this will not suffice against a healthy extra pawn that White keeps. }
12. Nbd2 Rd8 13. Qe4
{ It is not intuitive to allow Bf5 with a tempo, and it might look scary, especially in Blitz and Rapid. However, this is the strongest move in the position as the bishop on f5 is not at all alarming for us. }
13... Bf5 14. Qf4
{ The queen finds its safe spot, and Ne4 is coming next.   Black will soon have to say goodbye to his pair of bishops, and the illusion of initiative will be gone. Meanwhile, White keeps his healthy extra pawn with no weakness on the board. }
