{ The seeming weakness of the c3-pawn is deceptive. It's easy for White to defend and makes White's center unassailable. }
8... Qc7 9. Bd2
{ Just defending the pawn.  9.Ne2  was also possible, but the knight, in fact, has different plans. }
9... Nc6 10. Nh3
{ Keeping the square g4 available for the queen and looking at f4 or g5, this knight is very flexible.   Black has a lack of space, worse development, worse center, and on top of everything now; his king will also not find a good place to hide. }
