{  } 1. e4 c5 2. c3 e6
{ This move intends to fight for the center by playing d5 next. } 3. d4
{ Given a chance, this move is our automatic reply. } 3... cxd4
{ This dubious move, abandoning the fight for the center at once, is strangely popular. Black just gets a bad version of the French Defense. }
4. cxd4 d5
{ Black needs to play this sooner or later; otherwise, 2...e6 would have made little sense. Now White gets the Advanced French in one of the best possible versions. }
5. e5
{ White grabs the center and thus the control of the game. The development of White's pieces will be easy and fluid, and Black will find it tricky to do the same.  The main difference to the Advance French @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.e4  e6  2.d4  d5  3.e5  c5  4.c3  is the availability of the square c3 for the white knight. In the Advance French, Black would never take cxd4 so quickly and allow White to play Nc3. }
5... Bb4+
{ As so often, this tempting check simply misplaces the bishop. Black should stick to the plan with ...Nc6 instead. }
6. Nc3 { Blocking the check with a natural developing move. } 6... Ne7
{ The follow-up, developing the kingside. Black is ready to castle, but the king's position on g8 will be far from safe. }
7. Bd3 { Eyeing on h7 and getting ready for the sudden attack to follow. } 7...
O-O
{ Following a dangerous plan. As mentioned, nothing good will come out of placing the king here. On the other hand, the king in the center was not looking bright either 😊. }
8. Qh5
{ Sometimes chess is a very simple game. The attack basically plays itself here }
8... Nf5
{ 8...Ng6  9.Nf3  h6  trying to prevent Ng5 is met with  10.Bxh6  gxh6  11.Qxh6  with a winning attack.   After  8...h6  9.g4  f6  trying to break out and prevent g5 we play  10.g5!  anyway with the point that after  10...fxg5  11.h4  g4  12.Ne2  we can shift the queen and rook onto the newly opened g-file. }
9. Nf3
{ And Black will soon collapse under a barrage of threats here. To start with, g4 is a very annoying threat to deal with. }
