10. Nb5
{ A fantastic counter fork trick. The entire line is based on this idea. Without this resource, we could not have entered this variation. }
10... Nc2+
{ The best bet Black has got.   10...Nxf3  11.Ke2  runs into a double threat of Kxf3 and Nc7.   10...Ne6  11.Bc4  Rc8  12.Bd5  gives White an excellent position as  12...Rc5  13.Bxb7  Rxb5  runs into another fork with  14.Bc6  😊.   Finally,  10...O-O-O  11.Nxd4  Rxd4  12.Be3  Rd6  loses the pawn with  13.Bxa7  as there is no way to trap the bishop with  13...b6  since White has  14.Ba6   Thus in all these variations White gets almost an winning position. }
