{ Finishing development completely. } 14... Rfd8 15. Bb1
{ A standard plan to exploit the misplacement of the queen on d6.   Engines give a significant advantage to White. Once again, let us go a bit deeper to get an idea of the upcoming middle game and improve our general chess understanding. }
15... Nd5
{ Planning to trade a few pieces to get some free space for his pieces. A typical plan while playing against IQP.   15...Na5  allows White to get an excellent square for his knight with  16.Ne5 }
16. h4
{ Different moves were available for gaining a superior position, but we wanted to show this typical plan for increasing the general understanding of such IQP positions.   White ignores Black's idea of taking on c3/e3 and prepares a kingside attack with Ng5. }
16... Nxc3
{ 16...Nxe3  17.Qxe3  makes it impossible for Black to stop the deadly d5-break, and he gets a losing position instantly.   16...h6  17.Qd3  highlights the weakness of h7, and once again, Black gets a losing position rapidly. }
17. bxc3
{ We got weakness on c3 and a3, while Black is coming under kingside attack. It is clear what will be more important😊. }
17... Na5
{ 17...Qxa3  18.Ng5  will expedite the resignation with a devastating kingside attack when soon there will be no one to protect the king. }
18. Ne5
{ Black's pieces are far from helping their King and Bxh7 threat is just a trailer of what is about to happen there😊. }
