14... Qxd4 15. Bxd4
{ We have two bishops, but the pawn on c3 needs protection. } 15... O-O 16.
O-O-O
{ A great strategical move! White keeps the king on the queenside to ensure there won't be the slightest issue to keep supporting the c3-pawn anytime.   We have a double-bishop advantage and can play on both wings. White gets an edge that will last for a long time and will keep annoying Black. }
