{ As Black chose to make us play Be3 before going for the cxd4-e6 setup, we take advantage of the same. The c1-square is available for the rook, so we build pressure against the c6-knight. This idea is unheard of and has never been played by any 2400+ players yet.   Apart from being strong, it should also have a great surprise and practical value.  9.Bd3  gets us to the line where we wanted to have our bishop on g5, not e3.  Although it is slightly better according to the engines, even with the bishop on e3, we felt this rare  9.Bb5  is precise and poses more practical problems to Black. }
