[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. c3 d5 3. exd5 Qxd5 4. d4 Nf6 5. Nf3 cxd4 6. cxd4 Nc6
{ The worst possible way to get both knights out. Not just Black allows White to gain a tempo with Nc3, but he also does not take any measures against the upcoming threat of d5.   Strong machines are already giving +3 for White 😊. }
7. Nc3 Qd6 { Keeping the e5-square available after White goes d5. } 8. d5 Ne5
9. Bf4 { White takes a massive lead in development. } 9... Nd3+
{ Black gets the bishop on f4, but it doesn't solve his development issues.  9...Nxf3  10.Qxf3  would not help fix that problem either. }
10. Bxd3 Qxf4 11. Bb5+
{ We don't mind trading the light-squared bishop as it will force a retreat for the knight on f6. }
11... Bd7 12. Bxd7+ Nxd7 13. O-O
{ Black is not on time to castle without giving up material as  13...g6  14.Re1  Bg7  runs into the catastrophic  15.d6  e6  16.Nd5  Qxd6  17.Nf6+  and Black loses a piece on d7 eventually. }
