{ Threatening to take on d5 and c5. } 14... Qxd1
{ 14...Ncd7  15.Qc2  , with the idea of Rad1 gives White a tempo and a pleasant position. }
15. Rfxd1 Ncd7
{ This position occurred in Drazic, S @@StartBracket@@2430@@EndBracket@@- Cheparinov, I @@StartBracket@@2681@@EndBracket@@ Bol 2015, and here White could simply continue with... }
16. Rac1 { Finishing development completely. } 16... Nd5 17. Bd2
{ Black is yet to connect his rooks. White threatens to play Na5 and pick up one bishop and White's advantage is obvious here. }
