{ This is a footstep to get a pleasant endgame. We could also keep the advantage by playing a full-fledged middlegame with  11.Bd3 }
11... Qe4 12. Qd4
{ In the game Shankland - Vidit, Prague 2022, White played  12.Bb5  but after  12...Kf8  , the pawn on g2 remained hanging, and White had to return Nf3 when Black was doing fine. }
12... Qxd4 13. Bxd4 { Black's pieces.... } 13... O-O
{ The most likely move we are going to face in the OTB game. Engine's top choice  13...Nd5  feels a bit counterintuitive and inhuman, as it allows  14.Bb5+  .  Engines calmly continue with  14...Kf8  and after  15.O-O-O  f6  16.Nd3  Kf7  17.Rhe1  look at the position without the engine and pick your color😊.  We will be on the same page, surely. Even the engines give minute numbers for White, but it would be hard to play for Black in a practical game. }
14. g3
{ Black is yet to solve the problem of his light-squared bishop, while White enjoys a risk-free position where he can play for two results. }
