11... exd5
{ The most popular move.   Black gets a bad bishop but tries to argue that his double bishop advantage would compensate for it. }
12. Nc3 { Putting pressure on the d5-pawn and stopping Nc6 development. } 12...
Na6
{ The only decent square available for the knight.   12...Nd7  13.e6  leaves Black with a bad bishop, a worse pawn structure, and a passive position. }
13. Be3
{ We are deviating from the standard theory of  13.Nb5  . We want to finish development and keep the bishop on e3 to avoid giving a tempo in the future with Nc7-Ne6.  The move  13.Nb5  was mentioned in Sebastian's course, and he gave the following variation  13.Nb5  dxe5  14.dxe5  Nc5  15.Bf4  a6  16.Nbd4  with an obvious advantage for White.  However, instead of the naive a6 if Black pins the b5 knight with @@StartFEN@@r2q1rk1/pb2bppp/1p6/1NnpP3/5B2/5N2/PP2QPPP/R2R2K1 b - - 2 15@@EndFEN@@  15...Ba6  we could not find an advantage as Black intends to meet  16.Nfd4  with  16...Ne6  with some liquidation to follow.   We also tried the stronger @@StartFEN@@r2q1rk1/pb2bppp/1p6/1NnpP3/8/5N2/PP2QPPP/R1BR2K1 w - - 1 15@@EndFEN@@  15.Nfd4  with the idea to play  15...a6  16.Nc3  and keep a microscopic edge, but we liked the text move @@StartFEN@@r2q1rk1/pb2bppp/np1p4/3pP3/3P4/2N2N2/PP2QPPP/R1BR2K1 w - - 2 13@@EndFEN@@  13.Be3  more, which is rare and poses more practical problems for Black. }
13... Nc7
{ Hard to imagine any other move. Including dxe5-dxe5 will only help White build pressure against the d5-pawn. }
14. Qd3
{ Vacating the e2-square for the knight to maneuver with Ne2-Nf4 in the future. }
14... Ne6
{ To gain a tempo with  14...Ba6  might be tempting but after  15.Qc2  the knight on c7 gets stuck to defend the pawn on d5. The bishop on a6 gets a diagonal where there is nothing to aim for, and the stuck knight on c7 blocks the c-file for the a8-rook in the future.  Including dxe5-dxe5 helps White to play against the IQP on d5 and gives a lovely d4-square. }
15. h3
{ Many other moves also give White a pleasant position.   The text move is one of the top choices of engines that underlines our advantage is more durable and static due to Black's bad bishop and a worse pawn structure.   We are not in a rush. The long-term plan could be to get the c3 knight to f5 via e2-g3. There are also plans in the queenside with a4-Nb5 and trade on d6.   It isn't easy to find the upside for Black in this position. }
