{ There is no time to play any slow moves. Before Black stops us from attacking, we must take the initiative. }
16... g6
{ With the rook on d8, it makes no sense to take on g5 and give White a tempo with Bxg5 attacking the rook. }
17. Qg4
{ White is going for the h7-pawn with Qh3.   17...Nxe5  18.Qh3  Bxg5  19.Bxg5  Rd5  20.Bf4  gets Black into a difficult position with an avalanche of threats like Be4/Qh4-Qf6/Re3-Re1/Bb3/Qg3 etc.  The king remains weak due to the disappearance of the dark-squared bishop. White's attack on the kingside is scary for Black, giving White a clear edge.  Even in a correspondence game, Black could not hold this position. }
