14. Nxd4 e6 { Finally, Black got the time to play some moves on the kingside. }
15. Nxc6
{ This more straightforward and easy-to-play move was played by the World Champion against Nepo in Skilling Open Rapid 2020.  Sebastian, in his Alapin course, suggests the move  15.Nb5  with the idea to play Qa4-Rd1 and keeps practical pressure. That is also a valid practical option. }
15... Qxc6 16. Qg4
{ Black struggles to finish his development on the kingside. We ensure the bishop does not move as the g7-pawn remains under attack. }
16... Nf6
{ In the Carlsen - Nepo game, Black opted for  16...h5  and after the simple  17.Qe2  Magnus was enjoying a great position when it is not easy to castle quickly for Black; meanwhile, White aims for Rd1-Na3-Nb5. }
17. Qe2
{ We keep a long-term edge till the endgame, thanks to the strategic push a4-a5-a6.   In any endgame, Black's queenside will be a headache. But for now, we are coming with Nd2-f3-d4/e5, and Black cannot find a single weakness in our camp.   It is a very easy position to play for White and equally annoying to play for Black. }
