Qxc4 { Now it is our turn to attack 😊. } 18... Qc7
{ It might be tempting for some dynamic players to opt for  18...Rd6  as spotting the only winning move for White, is not trivial there.   19.Re5!!  ensures Black queen won't return to defend the king, and there is no way Black can attack us while engines scream  +4. }
19. Qxf7
{ Engines at very high depth claim this position equal, but a few things we must understand.   First of all, Black must make this far on his own 😊.   Secondly, by no means is it clear how it is equal. We have three pawns for the piece, and the Black king is pretty exposed. The pawns on the queenside will start marching soon, and most crucially, it is so much easier to play from the White side here. }
